{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Log entries with the same trace ID are grouped together regardless of which microservice emitted them.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is the handoff between ingestion/parsing and correlation/grouping modules: a real bug is often grouping by (service, trace_id) instead of trace_id alone. A unit test of only the grouping function can miss wiring/state partition mistakes across modules. No OS/network/LLM dependency is required.","test_description":"Feed mixed-service JSON logs through the real local ingestion + normalization + correlation pipeline, then assert one combined group per trace ID across services (not split by service name).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The timeline view orders entries by timestamp, correctly handling clock skew of up to 500ms between services.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is primarily deterministic ordering/skew-tolerance logic. The key failure is comparator/normalization behavior on timestamp inputs, which can be caught at a single function/object boundary without I/O. Integration could help, but is not the minimum for this specific failure mode.","test_description":"Call the timeline ordering/skew-adjustment logic directly with synthetic entries from multiple services offset within and beyond 500ms, and assert expected final order and tie-handling.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.7,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A latency spike (p99 above 3x the baseline) is detected and flagged in the anomaly report.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The behavior includes both detection and report flagging, so the real boundary is between metrics aggregation (baseline/p99) and anomaly reporting modules. Pure unit tests of threshold math can miss lost/incorrect flag propagation. No real external infra or LLM dependency is needed.","test_description":"Run a local end-to-end analytics pass over deterministic log fixtures with known baseline and a constructed spike where p99 > 3x baseline; assert anomaly flag appears in the generated report with correct metric context.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Malformed JSON log entries are skipped without crashing the pipeline, and the count of skipped entries is reported.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This failure appears at parser → pipeline error-handling/reporting boundaries: parser exceptions, continuation logic, and skipped-count accounting must work together. A parser-only unit test does not prove pipeline survival or accurate skip reporting. No System/LLM requirement.","test_description":"Process a mixed batch of valid and malformed JSON entries through the real local pipeline, assert the run completes, valid entries continue downstream, and skipped-count equals malformed-count.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The tool handles a burst of 10,000 log entries per second without dropping entries or falling behind.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This depends on real runtime characteristics (throughput, scheduling, buffering/backpressure, possible subprocess/OS effects). Mocked timing or queues can hide real drops/lag. The minimum boundary to catch real failure is a system-level load test with real process execution.","test_description":"Run the actual tool process under a burst load generator at 10,000 structured entries/sec for a fixed window; measure ingest count vs output/correlated count, queue lag, and end-to-end delay to assert no drops and no sustained backlog growth.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.8,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
